org.jclif.type
Class CommandLineConfiguration

java.lang.Object
  org.jclif.type.CommandLineConfiguration

public class CommandLineConfiguration
extends java.lang.Object

CommandLineConfiguration class is used to define the command line inputs accepted by an application. This is the class from which we specify the accepted options, parameters and commands of an application.

Author:
Stephen Lou Banal <stephen.banal@gmail.com>
